{
  "id": "indus_fish_sign",
  "name": "Indus: Fish Sign (Parpola 'min/meen') Positional & Bigram Profile",
  "description": "P3: Tests Parpola's rebus hypothesis for the Indus fish sign (most frequent ~342 occurrences, sign 411 in Mahadevan numbering; signs 70/72 in Fuls numbering have M-rate ~0.87, identified as primary fish allographs in our April 7 analysis). Runs PositionalProfiler to get I/M/T rates for all signs, FreqCounter to rank by frequency, and NgramCounter (bigrams + trigrams) to see what precedes and follows the fish sign. Also runs the full structural atlas (Zipf + entropy + WSC) for comparison. If fish is medial with M-rate >0.70 and appears frequently after INITIAL determinatives, this supports the 'meen' (fish=star) rebus reading.",
